cdm570.name: cdm570
cdm570.contactinfo: Comtech EF Data Crop. 2114 W. 7th Street Tempe, AZ 85281 USA Tel: 480-333-2200 Fax: 480-333-2540 Web: http://www.comtechefdata.com
cdm570.description: Module Identity for both CDM-570 L-Band and IF-Band Satellite Modems.

cdm570SerialNumber.name: cdm570SerialNumber
cdm570SerialNumber.description: Used to query the unit 9-digit serial number. Unit returns its S/N in the form xxxxxxxxx.

cdm570Temperature.name: cdm570Temperature
cdm570Temperature.description: Unit returns the value of the internal temperature, in degrees Celsius.

cdm570TurboOption.name: cdm570TurboOption
cdm570TurboOption.description: Turbo option, where: 0 = None 1 = Turbo 2 = TPC/LDPC

cdm570DataRateOption.name: cdm570DataRateOption
cdm570DataRateOption.description: Data rate option, where: 0 = Base (512 kbps) 1 = Up to 2048 kbps 2 = Up to 5000 kbps 3 = Up to 9980 kbps

cdm570HigherOrderModulation.name: cdm570HigherOrderModulation
cdm570HigherOrderModulation.description: Higer order modulation, where: 0 = None 1 = 8-PSK/8-QAM 2 = 16-QAM 3 = 8-PSK/8-QAM and 16-QAM

cdm570IPOption.name: cdm570IPOption
cdm570IPOption.description: IP Controller card, where: 0 = None 1 = Installed

cdm570RSCodecOption.name: cdm570RSCodecOption
cdm570RSCodecOption.description: RS Codec Option, where: 0 = None 1 = Installed

cdm570FirmwareRevision.name: cdm570FirmwareRevision
cdm570FirmwareRevision.description: Unit returns the value of the internal software revision installed in the unit, in the form of: Boot: XXXXXX Bulk1: YYYYYY Bulk2: ZZZZZZ, where: XXXXXX = software version of boot YYYYYY = software version of bulk1 ZZZZZZ = software version of bulk2

cdm570IpAddress.name: cdm570IpAddress
cdm570IpAddress.description: The IP address for the 10/100 BaseTx Ethernet management port.

cdm570IpSubnetMask.name: cdm570IpSubnetMask
cdm570IpSubnetMask.description: The network prefix length for the 10/100 BaseTx Ethernet management port.

cdm570DefaultGateway.name: cdm570DefaultGateway
cdm570DefaultGateway.description: The IP address of the default gateway.

cdm570MacAddress.name: cdm570MacAddress
cdm570MacAddress.description: The MAC address of the Ethernet interface.

cdm570AccessListEnforcement.name: cdm570AccessListEnforcement
cdm570AccessListEnforcement.description: Enable or disable enforcement of the the access list. Note: Be sure that you have added the SNMP browser's/manager's IP Address to the access list before enabling access list filtering. Otherwise, the SNMP browser/manager will no longer be able to gain access to the unit.

cdm570AccessListTable.name: cdm570AccessListTable
cdm570AccessListTable.description: The table that holds the access list.

cdm570AccessListEntry.name: cdm570AccessListEntry
cdm570AccessListEntry.description: The entry for the access list table.

cdm570AccessListIndex.name: cdm570AccessListIndex
cdm570AccessListIndex.description: The index for the access list from 1..4.

cdm570AccessIPAddress.name: cdm570AccessIPAddress
cdm570AccessIPAddress.description: The IP addresses that can access the unit. The value of 0.0.0.0 means not defined.

cdm570AccessSubnetMaskLength.name: cdm570AccessSubnetMaskLength
cdm570AccessSubnetMaskLength.description: The subnet mask length of the IP address for the access list. Subnet mask can be from 8..32. The value of 0 means not defined.

cdm570SNMPTrapDestinationIpAddress1.name: cdm570SNMPTrapDestinationIpAddress1
cdm570SNMPTrapDestinationIpAddress1.description: The IP address were SNMP notifications (traps) are to be sent. This IP address should correspond to a SNMP manager or browser.

cdm570SNMPTrapDestinationIpAddress2.name: cdm570SNMPTrapDestinationIpAddress2
cdm570SNMPTrapDestinationIpAddress2.description: The IP address were SNMP notifications (traps) are to be sent. This IP address should correspond to a SNMP manager or browser.

cdm570SNMPTrapCommunity.name: cdm570SNMPTrapCommunity
cdm570SNMPTrapCommunity.description: The community that will be included in SNMP notifications (traps) that are sent from unit.

cdm570SNMPTrapVersion.name: cdm570SNMPTrapVersion
cdm570SNMPTrapVersion.description: The SNMP version that will be used when sending traps from the unit. SNMPv1 will send V1 traps. SNMPv2 will send V2 notifications.

cdm570TxFrequency.name: cdm570TxFrequency
cdm570TxFrequency.description: Transmit frequency for both CDM-570L (L-Band) modem and CDM-570 (IF-band) modems. L-Band is 950 MHz to 1950 MHz. IF-Band is 50 MHz to 90 MHz and 100 MHz to 180 MHz. Units = Hz. Resolution = 100 Hz.

cdm570TxDataRate.name: cdm570TxDataRate
cdm570TxDataRate.description: Tx data rate in bps (Varies based on chart below.) Units = bps Resolution = 1 bps FEC Type Modulation Code Rate Data Rate High Rate -------- ----------- ---------- --------------------- --------- None BPSK Uncoded 4.8 kbps to 3.0 Mbps None QPSK/OQPSK Uncoded 9.6 kbps to 5.0 Mbps Viterbi BPSK Rate 1/2 2.4 kbps to 1.5 Mbps Viterbi QPSK/OQPSK Rate 1/2 4.8 kbps to 3.0 Mbps Viterbi QPSK/OQPSK Rate 3/4 7.2 kbps to 4.5 Mbps Viterbi QPSK/OQPSK Rate 7/8 8.4 kbps to 5.0 Mbps Vit + RS BPSK Rate 1/2 2.4 kbps to 1.363 Mbps Vit + RS QPSK/OQPSK Rate 1/2 4.3 kbps to 2.727 Mbps Vit + RS QPSK/OQPSK Rate 3/4 6.5 kbps to 4.091 Mbps Vit + RS QPSK/OQPSK Rate 7/8 7.5 kbps to 4.666 Mbps Vit + RS 16-QAM Rate 3/4 13.0 kbps to 4.0 Mbps Vit + RS 16-QAM Rate 7/8 16.8 kbps to 4.666 Mbps TCM + RS 8-PSK Rate 2/3 8.7 kbps to 4.4 Mbps Turbo BPSK Rate 5/16 2.4 kbps to 0.937 Mbps Turbo BPSK Rate 21/44 2.4 kbps to 1.430 Mbps Turbo QPSK/OQPSK Rate 21/44 4.8 kbps to 2.860 Mbps Turbo QPSK/OQPSK Rate 3/4 7.2 kbps to 4.5 Mbps N/A Turbo QPSK/OQPSK Rate 7/8 8.4 kbps to 5.0 Mbps 5.25 Mbps Turbo QPSK/OQPSK Rate 0.95 9.1 kbps to 5.0 Mbps 5.667 Mbps Turbo 8-PSK/8-QAM Rate 3/4 10.8 kbps to 5.0 Mbps 6.75 Mbps Turbo 8-PSK/Q-QAM Rate 7/8 13.6 kbps to 5.0 Mbps 7.875 Mbps Turbo 8-PSK/Q-QAM Rate 0.95 15.3 kbps to 5.0 Mbps 8.5 Mbps Turbo 16-QAM Rate 3/4 14.4 kbps to 5.0 Mbps 9.0 Mbps Turbo 16-QAM Rate 7/8 16.8 kbps to 5.0 Mbps 9.98 Mbps

cdm570TxFECCodeRate.name: cdm570TxFECCodeRate
cdm570TxFECCodeRate.description: Transmit code rate, where 0 = Rate 5/16 (Turbo only) 1 = Rate 22/44 (Turbo only) 2 = Rate 1/2 3 = Rate 2/3 (8-PSK TCM or 16-QAM only) 4 = Rate 3/4 5 = Rate 7/8 6 = Rate 0.95 (Turbo only) 7 = Rate 1/1 (Uncoded or No FEC)

cdm570TxModType.name: cdm570TxModType
cdm570TxModType.description: Transmit modulation type, where: 0 = BPSK 1 = QPSK 2 = OQPSK 3 = 8-PSK 4 = 16-QAM (Turbo or Viterbi + RS only) 5 = 8-QAM Depending on FEC type, not all of these selections will be valid.

cdm570TxFECType.name: cdm570TxFECType
cdm570TxFECType.description: Transmit FEC type where: 0 = Uncoded 1 = Viterbi 2 = Viterbit + Reed-Solomon 5 = TCM + Reed-Solomon (Code Rate = 2/3) 6 = Turbo 7 = TPC/LDPC Depending on hardware, not all of these selections will be valid.

cdm570TxSpectrumInvert.name: cdm570TxSpectrumInvert
cdm570TxSpectrumInvert.description: Transmit spectrum invert selection, where: 0 = Normal 1 = Transmit spectrum inverted

cdm570TxDataInvert.name: cdm570TxDataInvert
cdm570TxDataInvert.description: Invert transmit data, where: 0 = Normal 1 = Inverted

cdm570TxClockSource.name: cdm570TxClockSource
cdm570TxClockSource.description: Transmit clock source, where: 0 = Internal 1 = Tx Terrestrial 2 = Loop-Timed

cdm570TxScrambler.name: cdm570TxScrambler
cdm570TxScrambler.description: Transmit scrambler state, where: 0 = Off 1 = On (Default scrambler type) 2 = On = IESS-315 (Turbo only)

cdm570TxPowerLevel.name: cdm570TxPowerLevel
cdm570TxPowerLevel.description: Transmit output power level for both CDM-570L (L-Band) modem and CDM-570 (IF-band) modem. CDM-570L power level is between -40 and 0 dBm. CDM-570 power level is between -25 and 0 dBm. Units = 0.1 dBm

cdm570TxCarrierState.name: cdm570TxCarrierState
cdm570TxCarrierState.description: Transmit carrier state, where: 0 = Off 1 = On 2 = RTI (Receive/Transmit Inhibit) The following values are query only: 3 = External Control (read only) 4 = BUC warm-up delay (read only) 5 = STDMA Burst (ready only)

cdm570TxSymbolRate.name: cdm570TxSymbolRate
cdm570TxSymbolRate.description: Tx symbol rate in symbols per second (sps) Units = symbols per second (sps) Resolution = 1 sps

cdm570RxFrequency.name: cdm570RxFrequency
cdm570RxFrequency.description: Receive frequency for both CDM-570L (L-Band) modem and CDM-570 (IF-band) modems. L-Band is 950 MHz to 1950 MHz. IF-Band is 50 MHz to 90 MHz and 100 MHz to 180 MHz. Units = Hz. Resolution = 100 Hz.

cdm570RxDataRate.name: cdm570RxDataRate
cdm570RxDataRate.description: Rx data rate in bps (Varies based on chart below.) Units = bps Resolution = 1 bps FEC Type Modulation Code Rate Data Rate High Rate -------- ----------- ---------- --------------------- --------- None BPSK Uncoded 4.8 kbps to 3.0 Mbps None QPSK/OQPSK Uncoded 9.6 kbps to 5.0 Mbps Viterbi BPSK Rate 1/2 2.4 kbps to 1.5 Mbps Viterbi QPSK/OQPSK Rate 1/2 4.8 kbps to 3.0 Mbps Viterbi QPSK/OQPSK Rate 3/4 7.2 kbps to 4.5 Mbps Viterbi QPSK/OQPSK Rate 7/8 8.4 kbps to 5.0 Mbps Vit + RS BPSK Rate 1/2 2.4 kbps to 1.363 Mbps Vit + RS QPSK/OQPSK Rate 1/2 4.3 kbps to 2.727 Mbps Vit + RS QPSK/OQPSK Rate 3/4 6.5 kbps to 4.091 Mbps Vit + RS QPSK/OQPSK Rate 7/8 7.5 kbps to 4.666 Mbps Vit + RS 16-QAM Rate 3/4 13.0 kbps to 4.0 Mbps Vit + RS 16-QAM Rate 7/8 16.8 kbps to 4.666 Mbps TCM + RS 8-PSK Rate 2/3 8.7 kbps to 4.4 Mbps Turbo BPSK Rate 5/16 2.4 kbps to 0.937 Mbps Turbo BPSK Rate 21/44 2.4 kbps to 1.430 Mbps Turbo QPSK/OQPSK Rate 21/44 4.8 kbps to 2.860 Mbps Turbo QPSK/OQPSK Rate 3/4 7.2 kbps to 4.5 Mbps N/A Turbo QPSK/OQPSK Rate 7/8 8.4 kbps to 5.0 Mbps 5.25 Mbps Turbo QPSK/OQPSK Rate 0.95 9.1 kbps to 5.0 Mbps 5.667 Mbps Turbo 8-PSK/8-QAM Rate 3/4 10.8 kbps to 5.0 Mbps 6.75 Mbps Turbo 8-PSK/Q-QAM Rate 7/8 13.6 kbps to 5.0 Mbps 7.875 Mbps Turbo 8-PSK/Q-QAM Rate 0.95 15.3 kbps to 5.0 Mbps 8.5 Mbps Turbo 16-QAM Rate 3/4 14.4 kbps to 5.0 Mbps 9.0 Mbps Turbo 16-QAM Rate 7/8 16.8 kbps to 5.0 Mbps 9.98 Mbps

cdm570RxFECCodeRate.name: cdm570RxFECCodeRate
cdm570RxFECCodeRate.description: Rx code rate, where 0 = Rate 5/16 (Turbo only) 1 = Rate 22/44 (Turbo only) 2 = Rate 1/2 3 = Rate 2/3 (8-PSK TCM or 16-QAM only) 4 = Rate 3/4 5 = Rate 7/8 6 = Rate 0.95 (Turbo only) 7 = Rate 1/1 (Uncoded or No FEC)

cdm570RxDemodType.name: cdm570RxDemodType
cdm570RxDemodType.description: Rx demodulation type, where: 0 = BPSK 1 = QPSK 2 = OQPSK 3 = 8-PSK 4 = 16-QAM (Turbo or Viterbi + RS only) 5 = 8-QAM Depending on FEC type, not all of these selections will be valid.

cdm570RxFECType.name: cdm570RxFECType
cdm570RxFECType.description: Rx FEC type where: 0 = Uncoded 1 = Viterbi 2 = Viterbit + Reed-Solomon 5 = TCM + Reed-Solomon (Code Rate = 2/3) 6 = Turbo 7 = TPC/LDPC Depending on hardware, not all of these selections will be valid.

cdm570RxEbNoAlarmPoint.name: cdm570RxEbNoAlarmPoint
cdm570RxEbNoAlarmPoint.description: Rx Eb/No alarm point in 0.1 dB, with a range between 0.1 dB and 16 dB. Units = 0.1 dB. Resolution = 0.1 dB.

cdm570RxSpectrumInvert.name: cdm570RxSpectrumInvert
cdm570RxSpectrumInvert.description: Rx spectrum inversion, where: 0 = Normal 1 = Rx spectrum inverted

cdm570RxDataInvert.name: cdm570RxDataInvert
cdm570RxDataInvert.description: Invert receive data, where: 0 = Normal 1 = Inverted

cdm570RxBufferSize.name: cdm570RxBufferSize
cdm570RxBufferSize.description: Rx buffer size, where: 0 = Buffer disabled (Clock mode = Rx satellite) 1 = +/- 1024 bits 2 = +/- 2048 bits 3 = +/- 4096 bits 4 = +/- 8192 bits 5 = +/- 16384 bits 6 = +/- 32786 bits 7 = +/- 128 bits 8 = +/- 256 bits 9 = +/- 512 bits

cdm570RxDescrambler.name: cdm570RxDescrambler
cdm570RxDescrambler.description: Rx descrambler state, where: 0 = Off 1 = On (default descrambler type) 2 = On - IESS-315 (Turbo only)

cdm570RxDemodAcqSweepWidth.name: cdm570RxDemodAcqSweepWidth
cdm570RxDemodAcqSweepWidth.description: Rx +/- acquisition sweep range of demodulator, in KHz, ranging from: +/- 1 to +/- 32 KHz (rates < 625 ksym/second) or +/- 1 to 200 KHz (rates >= 625 ksym/second).

cdm570RxSymbolRate.name: cdm570RxSymbolRate
cdm570RxSymbolRate.description: Rx symbol rate in symbols per second (sps) Units = symbols per second (sps) Resolution = 1 sps

cdm570FramingMode.name: cdm570FramingMode
cdm570FramingMode.description: Unit operating mode, where: 0 = Unframed 1 = EDMAC Framing 2 = EDMAC-2 Framing

cdm570EDMACMode.name: cdm570EDMACMode
cdm570EDMACMode.description: EDMAC mode, where: 0 = EDMAC Idle 1 = EDMAC Master 2 = EDMAC Slave

cdm570EDMACAddress.name: cdm570EDMACAddress
cdm570EDMACAddress.description: For a Master, the EDMA Address is the range of addresses of distant-end units (modems or transceivers) which this unit, as the Master, will forward messages for. Only values which are integer multiples of ten are permitted. (10, 20, 30, 40, etc....) For a Slave, the EDMAC address is the address of the slave and is query only.

cdm570AUPCEnable.name: cdm570AUPCEnable
cdm570AUPCEnable.description: AUPC mode enable/disable, where: 0 = Disable 1 = Enable Note: To enable AUPC, framing must FIRST be enabled.

cdm570AUPCRemoteDemodTargetEbNo.name: cdm570AUPCRemoteDemodTargetEbNo
cdm570AUPCRemoteDemodTargetEbNo.description: Target Eb/No value for remote demod, from 0.0 to 14.9 dB. Units = 0.1 dB.

cdm570AUPCTxPowerMaxIncrease.name: cdm570AUPCTxPowerMaxIncrease
cdm570AUPCTxPowerMaxIncrease.description: Max increase in Tx Power permitted, from 0 to 9 dB. Units = dB.

cdm570AUPCActionOnMaxPower.name: cdm570AUPCActionOnMaxPower
cdm570AUPCActionOnMaxPower.description: Defines action on max. power condition, where: 0 = No action 1 = Generate Tx alarm

cdm570AUPCActionOnRemoteDemodUnlock.name: cdm570AUPCActionOnRemoteDemodUnlock
cdm570AUPCActionOnRemoteDemodUnlock.description: Defines action on remote demod unlock, where: 0 = Go to nominal power 1 = Go to max power

cdm570DataInterface.name: cdm570DataInterface
cdm570DataInterface.description: Terrestrial interface type, where: 0 = EIA-422/EIA-530 DCE 1 = V.35 DCE 2 = EIA-232 (sync) 3 = G.703 T1 AMI (forces Rx and Tx data rates to 1544 kbps) 4 = G.703 T1 B8ZS (forces Rx and Tx data rates to 1544 kbps) 5 = G.703 E1 Unbal AMI (forces Rx and Tx data rates to 2048 kbps) 6 = G.703 E1 Unbal HDB3 (forces Rx and Tx data rates to 2048 kbps) 7 = G.703 E1 Bal AMI (forces Rx and Tx data rates to 2048 kbps) 8 = G.703 E1 Bal HDB3 (forces Rx and Tx data rates to 2048 kbps) 9 = IP (Ethernet)

cdm570RTS.name: cdm570RTS
cdm570RTS.description: Defines how RTS/CTS will operate at the main data interface, where: 0 = RTS/CTS Loop, No Action (RTS and CTS are looped, so that CTS echoes the state of RTS, but RTS does not control the ON/OFF state of the carrier) 1 = Loop, RTS controls Tx Ouput (RTS and CTS are looped, so that CTS echoes the state of RTS and RTS controls the ON/OFF state of the carrier - the modem will not bring up its TX carrier until RTS is asserted.) 2 = Ignore RTS, Assert CTS Query Only: 3 = 1:N system in use, RTS/CTS ignored

cdm570T1LineBuildOut.name: cdm570T1LineBuildOut
cdm570T1LineBuildOut.description: Valid only for T1 interface, where: 0 = 0 - 133 feet 1 = 133 - 266 feet 2 = 266 - 399 feet 3 = 399 - 533 feet 4 = 533 - 655 feet

cdm570ReferenceFrequency.name: cdm570ReferenceFrequency
cdm570ReferenceFrequency.description: External reference frequency, where: 0 = Internal 10 MHz 1 = External 1 MHz 2 = External 2 MHz 3 = External 5 MHz 4 = External 10 MHz 5 = External 20 MHz

cdm570AlarmMaskTxFIFO.name: cdm570AlarmMaskTxFIFO
cdm570AlarmMaskTxFIFO.description: Tx FIFO alarm mask, where: 0 = Unmasked 1 = Masked

cdm570AlarmMaskG703BPV.name: cdm570AlarmMaskG703BPV
cdm570AlarmMaskG703BPV.description: G.703 BPV alarm mask, where: 0 = Unmasked 1 = Masked

cdm570AlarmMaskTxAIS.name: cdm570AlarmMaskTxAIS
cdm570AlarmMaskTxAIS.description: Tx-AIS alarm mask, where: 0 = Unmasked 1 = Masked

cdm570AlarmMaskRxAGC.name: cdm570AlarmMaskRxAGC
cdm570AlarmMaskRxAGC.description: Rx AGC alarm mask, where: 0 = Unmasked 1 = Masked

cdm570AlarmMaskEbNoAlarm.name: cdm570AlarmMaskEbNoAlarm
cdm570AlarmMaskEbNoAlarm.description: Eb/No alarm mask, where: 0 = Unmasked 1 = Masked

cdm570AlarmMaskRxAIS.name: cdm570AlarmMaskRxAIS
cdm570AlarmMaskRxAIS.description: Rx-AIS alarm mask, where: 0 = Unmasked 1 = Masked

cdm570AlarmMaskBufferSlip.name: cdm570AlarmMaskBufferSlip
cdm570AlarmMaskBufferSlip.description: Buffer slip alarm mask, where: 0 = Unmasked 1 = Masked

cdm570AlarmMaskExtReference.name: cdm570AlarmMaskExtReference
cdm570AlarmMaskExtReference.description: External reference alarm mask, where: 0 = Unmasked 1 = Masked

cdm570UnitAlarms.name: cdm570UnitAlarms
cdm570UnitAlarms.description: Modem Unit Faults: Value Description of unit fault 0 No faults 1 +5 Volt power supply 2 +12 Volt power supply 3 -5 Volt power supply 4 +23 Volt power supply 5 -12 Volt power supply 6 Tx synthesizer lock 7 Rx 1st LO synthesize lock 8 Rx 2nd LO synthesize lock 9 Ref PLL lock 14 MPP50 (IP Module) Fault 15 EEPROM checksum error

cdm570TxAlarms.name: cdm570TxAlarms
cdm570TxAlarms.description: Modem TX Traffic Faults: Value Description of Tx Traffic status 0 Tx traffic OK 1 No clock from terrestrial interface 3 Tx FIFO slip 5 Loss of External Reference 7 AUPC upper limit reached 9 AIS Detected on incoming data 11 Bipolar violation on G.705 interface

cdm570RxAlarms.name: cdm570RxAlarms
cdm570RxAlarms.description: Modem RX Traffic Faults Value Description of status parameter 0 Rx Traffic OK 1 Demodulator unlocked 3 AGC Alarm - signal out of range 5 RS Frame sync alarm 7 EDMAC Frame sync alarm 10 Buffer underflow 11 Buffer overflow 13 Eb/No alarm 15 AIS detected on incoming data

cdm570RxBERMultiplier.name: cdm570RxBERMultiplier
cdm570RxBERMultiplier.description: Estimated corrected BER. The BER is calculated by mubliplying the Multiplier by 10E-10. Calculuation: RxBER = (Multiplier) * 0.0000000001 Returns 2147483647 (max int) if demod is unlocked.

cdm570BufferFillState.name: cdm570BufferFillState
cdm570BufferFillState.description: Unit returns the value of the buffer fill state, between 1 to 99%. Returns 0 if demodulator is unlocked. Returns -1 if buffer is disabled.

cdm570RxFrequencyOffset.name: cdm570RxFrequencyOffset
cdm570RxFrequencyOffset.description: Unit returns the value of the measured frequency offset of the carrier being demodulated in Hz. Units = Hz. Resolution 100 Hz. Range = -200,000 Hz to 0 Hz and 0 Hz to 200,000 Hz.

cdm570RxSignalLevel.name: cdm570RxSignalLevel
cdm570RxSignalLevel.description: Unit returns the value of the Rx signal level, in dBm, between -99 dBm and -5 dBm. Returns -100 if signal is less than -99 dBm. Returns -4 if signal is greater than -5 dBm.

cdm570RxEbNo.name: cdm570RxEbNo
cdm570RxEbNo.description: Unit returns the value of Eb/No, between 0 and 16 db. Units = 0.1 dB. Resolution 0.1 dB. Returns 999 if demod is unlocked. For values greater than 16 dB, the reply will be 160.

cdm570StoredEventsEntry.name: cdm570StoredEventsEntry
cdm570StoredEventsEntry.description: The entry for the stored events table.

cdm570EventIndex.name: cdm570EventIndex
cdm570EventIndex.description: The index for stored events table.

cdm570EventDate.name: cdm570EventDate
cdm570EventDate.description: The date of the event in the form ddmmyy, where dd = day of the month (01 to 31) mm = month (01 to 12) yy = year (00 to 99)

cdm570EventTime.name: cdm570EventTime
cdm570EventTime.description: The time of the event in the form hhmmss, indicating the time from midnight, where: hh = hours (00 to 23) mm = minutes (00 to 59) ss = seconds (00 to 59)

cdm570EventDescription.name: cdm570EventDescription
cdm570EventDescription.description: The event description string with following format: {1 of the following: Clear, Fault, Info} - {Texual Description of Event}

cdm570ClearAllStoredEvents.name: cdm570ClearAllStoredEvents
cdm570ClearAllStoredEvents.description: Forces the software to clear the event log. This is a command only.

cdm570StatisticsSampleInterval.name: cdm570StatisticsSampleInterval
cdm570StatisticsSampleInterval.description: Used to set the sample interval for the statistics logging function, where the enumerated lists goes from 0 to 9 in 10 minute steps. Setting 0 disables the statistics logging function.

cdm570StatisticDate.name: cdm570StatisticDate
cdm570StatisticDate.description: The date of the statistic in the form ddmmyy, where: dd = day of the month (01 to 31) mm = month (01 to 12) yy = year (00 to 99)

cdm570StatisticTime.name: cdm570StatisticTime
cdm570StatisticTime.description: The time of the statistic in the form hhmmss, indicating the time from midnight, where: hh = hours (00 to 23) mm = minutes (00 to 59) ss = seconds (00 to 59)

cdm570StatisticMinEbNo.name: cdm570StatisticMinEbNo
cdm570StatisticMinEbNo.description: Minimum Eb/No during sample period. Units = 0.1 dB. Returns 999 if demod was unlocked during sample period.

cdm570StatisticAvgEbNo.name: cdm570StatisticAvgEbNo
cdm570StatisticAvgEbNo.description: Minimum Eb/No during sample period. Units = 0.1 dB. Returns 999 if demod was unlocked during sample period.

cdm570StatisticMaxTxPowerIncrease.name: cdm570StatisticMaxTxPowerIncrease
cdm570StatisticMaxTxPowerIncrease.description: Max. Tx power level increase during sample period. Units = 0.1 dB

cdm570StatisticAvgTxPowerIncrease.name: cdm570StatisticAvgTxPowerIncrease
cdm570StatisticAvgTxPowerIncrease.description: Average Tx power level increase during sample period. Units = 0.1 dB

cdm570ClearAllStoredStatistics.name: cdm570ClearAllStoredStatistics
cdm570ClearAllStoredStatistics.description: Forces the software to clear the statistics log. This is a command only.

cdm570AUPCRemoteDemodEbNo.name: cdm570AUPCRemoteDemodEbNo
cdm570AUPCRemoteDemodEbNo.description: Returns the value of the Eb/No ofthe remote demodulator. Units = 0.1 dB Responds 999 = remote demod unlocked. Responds 0 = EDMAC is disabled.

cdm570AUPCTxPowerIncrease.name: cdm570AUPCTxPowerIncrease
cdm570AUPCTxPowerIncrease.description: Returns the increase in Tx power level, in 0.1 dB (from the nominal setting) due to the action of AUPC. Responds with 999 if AUPC is disabled.

cdm570UnitTestMode.name: cdm570UnitTestMode
cdm570UnitTestMode.description: Unit Test Mode where: 0 = Normal Mode 1 = IF Loopback 2 = Digital Loopback 3 = IO Loopback 4 = RF Loopback 5 = Tx CW 6 = Tx Alternating Pattern

cdm570ConfigurationSave.name: cdm570ConfigurationSave
cdm570ConfigurationSave.description: Causes the device to store the current modem configuration in configuration memory location defined by the argument (0 to 9). This is a COMMAND ONLY. Get always responds with 0.

cdm570ConfigurationLoad.name: cdm570ConfigurationLoad
cdm570ConfigurationLoad.description: Causes the device to retrieve a previously stored modem configuration from configuration memory location defined by the argument (0 to 9). This is a COMMAND ONLY. Get always responds with 0.

cdm570ReCenterBuffer.name: cdm570ReCenterBuffer
cdm570ReCenterBuffer.description: Forces the software to recenter the receive Plesiochronous/Doppler buffer. This is a command only.

cdm570RTCDate.name: cdm570RTCDate
cdm570RTCDate.description: A date in the form dd/mm/yy, where dd = day of the month (01 to 31) mm = month (01 to 12) yy = year (00 to 99)

cdm570RTCTime.name: cdm570RTCTime
cdm570RTCTime.description: A time in the form hh:mm:ss, indicating the time from midnight, where: hh = hours (00 to 23) mm = minutes (00 to 59) ss = seconds (00 to 59)

cdm570WarmUpDelay.name: cdm570WarmUpDelay
cdm570WarmUpDelay.description: Warm-up delay for internal frequency reference (OCXO), where: 0 = Disabled (instant on - no delay for OCXO to reach temperature) 1 = Enabled (unit waits until OCXO reaches correct temperature)

cdm570WarmUpCountdown.name: cdm570WarmUpCountdown
cdm570WarmUpCountdown.description: As a query, returns the Warm-up delay countdown in seconds remaining. As a command, only takes the argument 0 and is used to truncate the warm-up delay period to zero, forcing the unit into 'instanct-on' mode.

cdm570CircuitID.name: cdm570CircuitID
